@node "1" "Introduction" 

At first, sorry for my poor English. English is not my native langue!!!
=======================================================================


Some questions for you:


1. Do you play games on the MacIntosh under emulation?

2. Do you hate play via keyboard?

3. Do you have the CD32 joypad?


If your answer is three times yes, then you maybe know program @{"  MacJoy  "  LINK "11"}.
This program is super but his configuration is very ugly :(

But don't cry. MacJoyPadGUI is here :)

Features:

 · Simple GUI for easy usage a configure all keys of CD32 joypad.

 · Save and load configuration

 · Info about configuration

 · Works even with classic joystic (with limitation)


@endnode


@node "2" "Requirements"

MacJoPadGUI  should  works  on  any Amiga 1200 with system OS3.0 or higher.
Simply,  if  works  Shapeshifter or Fusion on your Amiga, then MacJoyPadGUI
wil works too :)


Other requirements: 

 
 · lowlevel.library (includet in OS3.1)

 · topaz.font in directory SYS:fonts (strongly recommendet)

 · Resolution 640 x 480 (recommendet, but not required)

 · Program    MacJoy1.3    (you can find Aminet in directory
   misc/emu/MacJoy13.lha)


@endnode


@node "3" "Installation"

Simply unpack the archive and copy program's drawer wherewer you want.

Program MacJopPad must be in directory SYS:C.  Don't rename this file!


It's all :)


@endnode


@node "4" "Usage"

If  program  is  launching  then  main window is appear.  If this window is
active, you can set keys.

How?  It's very easy!

1.  Press one button of CD32 joypad.

2.  Selected button change colour on window.

3.  Press key on keyboard.

4.  Go on step 1


One  CD32  button you can set on more keys on keypboard.  If you set second
same keys, screen is flashing.


@{U}@{B}Other settings:@{UU}@{UB}


@{B}Misc@{B} and @{UB}Led@{UB} - special settings of MacJoyPad (see manual of MacJoyPad)


@{B}Sav  keys@{UB}  -  save actual config on disc.   Misc and Led will save too.
Recommendet for save is directory Keys on program's drawer.


@{B}Load keys@{UB} - load actual config from disc.

If  MacJoyPadGUI  launch,  configuration named default is load.  If you use
any config often, you can use default config as your basic config.

If file default not exists, MacJoyPadGUI make this file without loading.

Default settings is default settings of MacJoyPad


@{B}Info@{UB}  -  info about actual configuration. If you want change this info, you
must  edit  this  file  manually.   MacJoPadGUI  don't support edit info in
actual version.


How edit info ?  (step by step):


1.  Set keys and save configuration.

2.  Launch your favorit ASCII editor (eg CygnusED, GoldED, ED ...).

3.  Edit info.

a) info must be between two lines:

=================== Place for your info ===================|

and

==================== End of your info =====================|

Don't edit other lines.


b)  Max  length  of  line  must be 60 and max number of columns must be 40.
Other will be cut off.

c) Don't use sign | .  This sign use MacJoyPadGUI as end of line.

4.  Save config.


@{B}Run MacJoyPad@{UB}  -  launch MacJoyPad with selected settings. If MacJoyPad run
correctly then requester appear.

@{B}End of MacJopadGUI@{UB}  -  program  quits  if you push standard close gadget on
left  up  corner.   Before is ending, MacJoyPadGUI check if MacJoPad run on
memory.  If run, then requester appear.

If  you want remove MacJoyPad from memory later, simply launch MacJoyPadGUI
again, push close gadged and select YES if requester appear.


@endnode


@node "5" "Tips"

 ·  Launch  MacJoyPadGUI  before launch Mac emulator and quit  MacJoyPadGUI
    before end Mac emulator.

 · If you have edited preference settings, backup original file.

 · Try Macintosh Garden  on  http://mac.the-underdogs.org/ .   On this  WWW
   you  canfind  more  games for your emulator (eg.  Out of This World (aka
   Another World), FlashBack, Loderunner, Wolfenstein 3D, Sensory Overload,
   Blackthorne and many others).

 · Some games from Mac allow configure keys direct in program.  You can use
   only one preference file for more games.

 · Some bonus configuration files from autor of MacJoyPadGUI you can find
   in directory Keys in program's drawer.  Enjoy it.

 · Don't forget that MacJoyPad works with all system friendly games.  Not
   only with games for Mac emulation.

 · If you don't have CD32 joypad, you can use classic joystick too.  But
   only for 5 or 6 buttons (4x cross and max 2x fire).


@endnode


