@node "11" "MacJoy1.3"


         MacJoy & MacJoyPad by Francesco Doro (fdoro@gpnet.it)

  In this archive you find two small utilities that allow using joystick
and joypad with the Macintosh emulators ShapeShifter and Emplant (probably
but not tested also AMax IV).

  Use MacJoy for joystick and MacJoyPad for CD32 joypad.  Read docs to
learn how you can configure them.

  Both utilities remap joystick or joypad events to keyboard events.  Since
all mac games give at least keyboard support it is now possible to play
them using these devices.  Try them and you will see that it's exactly like
play an Amiga game with real joystick support.

  These utilities probably can be useful also for some Amiga applications
or other emulators, they work for every application that uses the Amiga OS.
I did everything possible to make them compatible and OS friendly; I have
not used any hack or illegal patch.

  Both utilities require Kickstart 2.0 or better.  MacJoyPad requires
lowlevel.library in the LIBS:  path; this library is not included since it
is copyright.

  Read respective docs to see credits.

  Sorry for bad english in this and other docs.

History:

1.0 (15-8-95):
  First release, only joystick support.

1.1 (30-9-95):
  Added MacJoyPad for CD32 joypad. MacJoy still present unchanged.

1.2 (31-10-95):
  MacJoy: unchanged.
  MacJoyPad:
  - Added automatic detection joystick/joypad (thanks to Thomas Kessler).
  - Added CLI interface with standard AmigaDOS aguments parsing.
  - Now checks whether already active.
  - Some optimizations.

1.3 (10-1-96):
  MacJoy: unchanged.
  MacJoyPad:
  - Fixed a big bug (occurred only if it was launched twice)
  - Now if launched from shell or script it doesn't open any window
  - Added LED option to turn audio filter off
  - Changed default config (not safe to have a Return key in the joypad...)


Note:
  Version number is referred to the archive version.  For example in v1.3
you find MacJoy v1.0 and MacJoyPad v1.2.


@endnode